ic description of the use of the English subjunctive in main clauses, noun clauses, relative clauses, and adverbial clauses. It explores the factors which governed its competition with other verbal expressions in texts ranging from the 9th to the beginning of the 18th century. Employing close reading alongside analysis of corpus data and the use of descriptive statistics, it offers new insights into the research landscape of English subjunctive use and into the fields of historical English linguistics and corpus linguistics.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Jun 2022) 0aEnglish languageyEarly modern, 1500-1700xSubjunctive. 0aEnglish languageyMiddle English, 1100-1500xSubjunctive. 0aEnglish languageyOld English, ca. 450-1100xModality. 0aEnglish languageyOld English, ca. 450-1100xMood. 0aEnglish languageyOld English, ca. 450-1100xSubjunctive. 4aLanguage & Linguistics. 7aLANGUAGE ARTS & DISCIPLINES / Linguistics / General.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEdinburgh University Press Complete eBook-Package 2020z97831107804130 cprintz978147443799840uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9781474438018?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781474438018423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781474438018/original  a978-3-11-078041-3  Edinburgh University Press Complete eBook-Package 2020b2020  aEBA_CL_LS  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_LS  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK